Students at a school in Memphis were suspended after sharing a mugshot of their teacher on Instagram .
Children posted the police picture of eighth grade teacher Tiffany Jackson on social media on Friday , after she was arrested for driving with an invalid licence .
When the authorities of Highland Oaks Middle School in Tennessee realised the image had been shared online , they suspended three of the students for three days .
School officials said the children had demonstrated an ` inappropriate use of electronic media .